Package: CoMorTrax
Type: Package
Title: Comorbidity-Aware Multi-Scale Transcriptomic Analysis Framework
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2026-03-23
Authors@R: person("Ahmed", "Mokhtar", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "ahmed.salem@bioinformatics.org",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Author: Ahmed Mokhtar [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Ahmed Mokhtar <ahmed.salem@bioinformatics.org>
Description: CoMorTrax is a multi-label comorbidity modeling framework for
    single-cell transcriptomic data. It provides a complete analytical
    pipeline for modeling comorbid disease interactions at single-cell
    resolution, including multi-label disease encoding, comorbidity-aware
    differential expression, interaction effect quantification (synergistic,
    antagonistic, additive), pathway-level enrichment, cell-type vulnerability
    scoring, gene regulatory network rewiring analysis, machine-learning-based
    comorbidity state prediction, and optional spatial transcriptomics mapping.
    Unlike conventional tools that analyze each disease independently,
    CoMorTrax explicitly captures non-additive molecular crosstalk using
    permutation-based interaction scoring.
